                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00111 A.R./1068: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-15T20:00:00-03:30"
                            >May 15, 1940—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 15—8 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>70. My 69, May 15, 11 a.m. Guani has just informed me that Cantilo accepts the
                    Uruguayan draft and withdraws his proposed modification to Buenos Aires and Rio
                    de Janeiro.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Buenos Aires.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
